OL,3,CFormer chief constable to face
OL,4,Cmisconduct hearing over workplace sex
OL,5,Callegations
OL,7,F"We investigated allegations relating
OL,8,Fto two sexual relationships in the
OL,9,Fworkplace that he failed to disclose.
OL,10,FThe first was before he became chief
OL,11,Fconstable and the second was after his
OL,12,Fappointment."
OL,14,FThe IOPC said that Mr Chilton is
OL,15,Falleged to have "failed to disclose a
OL,16,Fprevious sexual relationship with
OL,17,Fanother officer during the application
OL,18,Fprocess to become chief constable".
